Houston Lighting and Power Co, a unitof Houston Industries Inc, said it will redeem on May 4 at parplus accrued interest about 140 mln dlrs of first mortgagebonds.    The utility expects the redemption will save it nearlythree mln dlrs annually in interest expenses. Houston Lightingrecently exchanged 390 mln dlrs of high coupon bonds for ninepct bonds, saving about 11 mln dlrs in annual interest costs.    Houston Lighting plans to buy back its outstanding 11-1/4pct bonds of 2009, 12s due 2010, 12-3/8s of 2013 and 11-5/8sdue 2015 and part of its 10-1/8s of 2004. Reuter&#3;